---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import profilePhoto from '../assets/images/profile.jpg';
---

<BaseLayout title="About">
  <article class="prose-custom">
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start sm:items-center gap-8 mb-8">
        <Image
          src={profilePhoto}
          alt="Tim Pepper"
          width={160}
          height={160}
          class="w-32 h-32 sm:w-40 sm:h-40 rounded-full object-cover flex-shrink-0 ring-2 ring-accent-cyan/40"
        />
        <div>
          <h1 class="text-5xl font-display font-bold leading-tight mb-3">
            Tim Pepper
          </h1>
          <p class="text-xl" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
            Engineering leader building inclusive teams and shipping pragmatic software.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 mb-8">
        <a href="/posts" class="inline-flex items-center font-mono text-sm px-4 py-2 rounded border border-accent-cyan text-accent-cyan hover:bg-accent-cyan hover:text-black transition-colors">
          Read the posts
        </a>
        <a href="#connect" class="inline-flex items-center font-mono text-sm px-4 py-2 rounded border hover:border-accent-cyan hover:text-accent-cyan transition-colors" style="border-color: var(--border);">
          Let's connect
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="h-px bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-accent-cyan to-transparent mb-12 opacity-30"></div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-12">
      <div class="rounded border p-4" style="border-color: var(--border);">
        <p class="font-mono text-xs mb-1" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">Experience</p>
        <p class="font-display text-xl font-semibold">10+ years</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded border p-4" style="border-color: var(--border);">
        <p class="font-mono text-xs mb-1" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">Current focus</p>
        <p class="font-display text-xl font-semibold">Engineering Leadership</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded border p-4" style="border-color: var(--border);">
        <p class="font-mono text-xs mb-1" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">Community</p>
        <p class="font-display text-xl font-semibold">Board Member @ WILD</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-6 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        I'm Tim Pepper. I've worked in software development for over a decade, most recently as a practice lead for software engineering.
      </p>

      <p>
        I write about leadership, engineering practice, and what it looks like to return to hands-on craft after years of leading teams.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-display font-semibold border-l-4 border-accent-cyan pl-4 my-8">
        How I Help Teams
      </h2>

      <p>
        As a tech leader, I focus on building inclusive, high-performing teams whilst
        delivering complex software projects that actually work. I also love creating environments where 
        people can do their best work.
      </p>

      <p>
        My technical background is <strong>broad</strong>... starting with Java and mobile development within Healthcare, expanding into 
        JavaScript/TypeScript fullstack work in Retail and Health settings. I've worked primarily in Azure with stints in AWS and 
        Cloudflare. I've touched everything from .NET to Vue.js to Kotlin. Lately, I've been tinkering with AI to see what's actually useful versus what's just hype.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-display font-semibold border-l-4 border-accent-cyan pl-4 my-8">
        Community & Inclusion
      </h2>

      <p>
        I'm a big EDI advocate with a focus on gender and LGBTQ+ inclusion, 
        having run a team of diversity and inclusion champions, I work to make tech more welcoming and 
        accessible. I'm a board member for Women in Digital Leeds, and I've been fortunate to 
        speak at events and win awards for this work. Community and inclusivity aren't just "nice to have" for me, they're central to how I lead 
        and what I value.
      </p>

      <p>
        I'm also a big video game and music nerd with an MA in philosophy. Love some live comedy and you might find me behind the mic if you're lucky!
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-display font-semibold border-l-4 border-accent-cyan pl-4 my-8">
        What You'll Find Here
      </h2>

      <p>
        Pepper Headspace is my attempt to think out loud. I want a place to reflect on leadership 
        lessons, share what I'm learning (and unlearning), explore technical 
        rabbit holes, and occasionally talk about the weird projects and interests that don't fit 
        neatly into a LinkedIn profile.
      </p>

      <p>
        Writing helps me process. If it helps you too, whether you're a fellow leader trying to 
        navigate consultancy, an engineer thinking about your next step, or someone just curious 
        about how this all works, then I'll call that a win.
      </p>

      <h2 id="connect" class="text-3xl font-display font-semibold border-l-4 border-accent-cyan pl-4 my-8">
        Let's Connect
      </h2>

      <p>
        I'd love to hear from you. Whether you want to chat about tech leadership, share your own 
        experiences with diversity and inclusion in tech, or just say hi, reach out.
      </p>

      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a href="mailto:tim.pepper04@gmail.com" class="inline-flex items-center font-mono text-sm px-4 py-2 rounded border border-accent-cyan text-accent-cyan hover:bg-accent-cyan hover:text-black transition-colors">
          Email me
        </a>
        <a href="/posts" class="inline-flex items-center font-mono text-sm px-4 py-2 rounded border hover:border-accent-cyan hover:text-accent-cyan transition-colors" style="border-color: var(--border);">
          Browse posts
        </a>
      </div>

      <ul class="space-y-2 ml-6">
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:tim.pepper04@gmail.com" class="underline decoration-accent-cyan decoration-2 underline-offset-4 hover:text-accent-cyan transition-colors">tim.pepper04@gmail.com</a></span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span><strong>LinkedIn:</strong> <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/tim-pepper-214370181/" class="underline decoration-accent-cyan decoration-2 underline-offset-4 hover:text-accent-cyan transition-colors">Connect with me</a></span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span><strong>GitHub:</strong> <a href="https://github.com/tpepper0408" class="underline decoration-accent-cyan decoration-2 underline-offset-4 hover:text-accent-cyan transition-colors">See what I'm building</a></span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span><strong>WILD Digital (Board Member):</strong> <a href="https://www.wild-digital.tech/" class="underline decoration-accent-cyan decoration-2 underline-offset-4 hover:text-accent-cyan transition-colors">Learn more about our work at WILD Digital</a></span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t" style="border-color: var(--border);">
        <p class="text-base" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
          This site is built with Astro and Tailwind CSS. The code is available on GitHub if you're 
          curious about how it works or want to build something similar.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
